 View Job Cart

Product Manager
Job Posting Number: 166652
Marketing Shelton, CT June 27, 2017
Apply Add to Cart


About the Opportunity

As a Senior Product Manager you will work to innovate and lead in the mailing and communications space. With the expanding role of digital communications, we are growing existing businesses, and launching new ones to ensure our clients can communicate the digital landscape evolves. The Senior Product Manager is responsible for owning the clients’ end-to-end experience, driving their products from concept to delivery, and being accountable for the delivery of planned global business results. Your career with Pitney Bowes will help you succeed by providing a competitive salary and benefits, extensive training, and a high profile career path for successful performers. This position is located in Shelton, Connecticut.


Build. Deploy. Bridge. Grow.
 
In this role, you’ll join our Small/Medium Business (SMB) Solutions team and report to the Director, SMB Software & Services. You will be responsible for:


Understand our customers’ needs and motivations, and champion the “voice of the customer” internally.
Build, maintain, and drive a clear and prioritized roadmap for delivering a product that maintains a dominant position in the marketplace.  May include pursuing new channel strategies, partner relationships and models, or internal development. 
Understand and analyze the market, including industry trends, the position of our competitors, and potential opportunities and threats to our strategy. Define a strategy to stay ahead of the competition and optimize our market opportunity.
Demonstrated success in P&L management and being accountable in driving the attainment of planned global revenue and profit for assigned portfolio.
Proven experience launching and growing commercially successful web-based applications or SaaS offerings.
Experience leading cross-functional teams to deliver results.
Experience defining relevant success metrics, and using data to influence decisions. Includes developing and presenting business cases, and tracking post-launch performance.
Ability to “dig in” and understand the root cause of a problem, define potential options for solving the problem, and make decisions for both the short and long terms. 
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills and an ability to communicate complicated ideas in a clear and simple way both internal and externally.


Qualifications


Bachelor’s degree, MBA preferred
5-7 years of experience in product management, managing software and services through the entire lifecycle.
Experience working with third-party partners.
Proven experience developing, launching and growing (including P&L responsibility) commercially successful software and services, especiallyweb-based applications or software
Experience with SaaS applications is highly desirable
Experience with addressing software and related US and Canadian postal regulations is highly desirable.



The Team

Within our Small/Medium Business (SMB) Solutions team, we provide a full range of mailing equipment and postage meters, maintenance and support services and supplies that enable our clients to efficiently create mail and evidence postage. We segment our SMB Solutions business between our North America operations, comprising the U.S. and Canadian businesses, and our International operations. We are a leading provider of postage meters and have approximately one million meters installed. 


Pitney Bowes is an Equal Employment Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer that values diversity and inclusiveness in the workplace. 


M/F/Veterans/Individuals with Disabilities/LGBT are encouraged to apply.


All interested individuals must apply online. Individuals with disabilities who cannot apply via our online application should refer to the alternate application options via our Individuals with Disabilities link.




 






 
