The Pitney Bowes Inc. (PBI) Given Consensus Recommendation of "Hold" by Brokerages
Xavier Trudeau
Juillet 24, 2017



Part












(NYSE:PBI). Lord Abbett & Communication Limited holds 1.16M shares or 0.05% of its portfolio.
Pitney Bowes Inc. has a 50 day moving average of 15.25 and a 200 day moving average of 14.45. It is down 15.45% since July 20, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 32.15% the S&P500. (PBI) have 185.98 million outstanding shares now held by all its shareholders, including share blocks held by institutional investors and restricted shares owned by the company's officers and insiders. General Mtrs Co (Put) now has $54.13 billion valuation. The stock declined 1.32% or $0.48 reaching $35.93 on the news. About 349,408 shares traded. Skyworks Solutions Inc (NASDAQ:SWKS) has risen 65.40% since July 21, 2016 and is uptrending.Pitney Bowes Inc. had its " rating reiterated by analysts at Brean Capital. The company has a market capitalization of $2.90 billion, a P/E ratio of 29.14 and a beta of 1.16. The Company offers customer information management, location intelligence and customer engagement products and solutions to help its clients market to their customers, and shipping, mailing, and cross border e-commerce products and solutions that enable the sending of parcels and packages across the globe.P/E ratio of the company is 28.57. The Company's divisions include Small & Medium Business Solutions, Enterprise Business Solutions and Digital Commerce Solutions. Therefore 41% are positive. On average, equities analysts predict that Pitney Bowes will post $1.74 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. The stock has a consensus rating of "Hold" and a consensus price target of $18.50.Among 22 analysts covering United States Steel Corporation (NYSE:X), 9 have Buy rating, 2 Sell and 11 Hold. Sidoti lowered shares of Pitney Bowes from a "buy" rating to a "neutral" rating in a research note on Monday, May 15th.Since May 17, 2017, it had 1 buy, and 0 selling transactions for $75,444 activity.In other Pitney Bowes news, Director Linda S. Sanford acquired 5,000 shares of Pitney Bowes stock in a transaction on Wednesday, May 17th.Investors sentiment increased to 1.52 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.62, from 0.9 in 2016Q3.Shares of Pitney Bowes Inc. Balyasny Asset Management Lc holds 0% or 13,340 shares. Comerica Bancshares holds 0.01% in Pitney Bowes Inc. (NYSE:PBI). 155,722 were accumulated by Chevy Chase Holdings. (NYSE:PBI). 4,000 are owned by Hall Laurie J Trustee.05/06/2015 - Pitney Bowes Inc. was upgraded to " by analysts at Zacks. The legal version of this piece can be viewed at https://www.themarketsdaily.com/2017/07/23/pitney-bowes-inc-pbi-upgraded-at-zacks-investment-research-updated-updated-updated.html. 34,333 are owned by Utah Retirement Sys. Credit Suisse Ag, Switzerland-based fund reported 624,611 shares. Goldman Sachs Gp owns 1.26 million shares for 0.01% of their portfolio. Mcmillion Cap invested in 0.13% or 12,200 shares. 57,105 are held by Carl Domino.Wolverine Asset Management Llc decreased Barclays Bk Plc (Put) stake by 369,100 shares to 613,300 valued at $15.65M in 2016Q4. It also reduced Verizon Communications Inc (NYSE:VZ) stake by 288,958 shares and now owns 15,542 shares.A number of analysts have recently commented on the company. Therefore 33% are positive. Skyworks Solutions Inc. had 67 analyst reports since July 27, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. Daiwa Securities downgraded General Motors Company (NYSE:GM) on Wednesday, January 11 to "Underperform" rating. ValuEngine downgraded Pitney Bowes from a "buy" rating to a "hold" rating in a research report on Friday, June 2nd. RSI is a technical indicator of price momentum, comparing the size of recent gains to the size of recent losses and establishes oversold and overbought positions. Five research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and one has assigned a buy rating to the stock. The firm earned "Buy" rating on Tuesday, August 16 by Nomura. The rating was upgraded by Suntrust Robinson on Thursday, April 20 to "Buy". The stock of General Motors Company (NYSE:GM) earned "Sector Perform" rating by RBC Capital Markets on Thursday, October 22. Deutsche Bank maintained General Motors Company (NYSE:GM) on Wednesday, October 14 with "Hold" rating. Its up 0.62, from 0.9 in 2016Q3. It dived, as 73 investors sold GM shares while 302 reduced holdings. 118 funds opened positions while 550 raised stakes. The company's stock had a trading volume of 1,316,020 shares. 179,523 were reported by Blume Cap. Institutional investors own 77.96% of the company's stock. Sg Americas Limited Com, New York-based fund reported 380,425 shares. 425,441 were reported by Gulf Interest Natl Bank (Uk). Bluemountain Cap Mngmt Ltd reported 932,015 shares. New Mexico Educational Retirement Board holds 0.25% or 151,900 shares in its portfolio. Highlander Mngmt Ltd Liability reported 307 shares. East Coast Asset Management Lc invested in 6,027 shares or 0.06% of the stock. During the same quarter in the prior year, the business posted $0.34 earnings per share.Receive News & Ratings Via Email - Enter your email address below to receive a concise daily summary of the latest news and analysts' ratings with our FREE daily email newsletter.

 




